magnitude.label: Magnitude/Relevance
magnitude.description: The relative size of the technology (in terms of investment, people involved, percentage of revenue)
magnitude.name: magnitude

experience.label: Experience/Maturity
experience.description: The relative time this technology has been around (for us)
experience.name: experience

rings.label: Out of Scope
rings.description: A technology we’re not addressing and we’re not foreseeing addressing in the near future.

rings.label: Potential
rings.description: A technology we’re not addressing now but plan to do it soon.

rings.label: Assess
rings.description: A technology we’re trying through internal or external PoCs, with no Production Deployments yet.

rings.label: Trial
rings.description: A technology in which we’re building a first project/MVP that is running in production or will run in production very soon. Not really sure if this is to become a full-fledge part of our Service Portfolio but has the potential.

rings.label: Adopt
rings.description: A technology in which we’ve built and (want to) continue to build and deliver new projects. . Must be strategic (something we believe will have a continuity in the near future, and in which we’ll invest in developing new business), not casuistic.

rings.label: Deprecate
rings.description: A technology we’ll no longer pursue or offer in our projects. We’ll not position or propose this offer proactively.
